:"How is it that the '''noema''' can be both a sense and the intented objectivity itself? Husserl distinguises three moments in the '''noema''': the [[thetic]] characteristic ('''noematic''' correlate of the act-quality), the ''''noematic'''' sense (the assimilation of the act-matter into the newly conceived intentional content), andd the determined X (the "inntermost moment" of the '''noema''').